0. ","index":"01399","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>Resolution agreed to.</i></b> ","index":"01400","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This concludes our consideration for the Estimates for the section\nof Committee of Supply meeting in the Chamber. ","index":"01401","speaker":""},{"html":"����� I would like to thank the ministers, critics and other honourable\nmembers for their hard work and dedication during this process. ","index":"01402","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Committee\nrise. ","index":"01403","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Call\nin the Speaker. ","index":"01404","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><span style=\"text-transform:uppercase\">IN\nSESSION</span></b>","index":"01405","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam Speaker:</b> As the hour is past 5:30, in accordance with\nsections 8, 13, 15 and 16 of the Sessional Order passed by the House on\nSeptember 30th, 2019, we shall now consider Bill 22, The Business Registration\nSupervision and Ownership Transparency Act (Various Acts Amended), beginning\nwith report stage and followed immediately by concurrence and third reading. ","index":"01406","speaker":""},{"html":"����� For the information of all members, any matters of privilege and\npoints of order would be deferred until after these actions have been\nconcluded. ","index":"01407","speaker":""},{"html":"����� For each report stage amendment, the sponsor will first move the\nmotion and I will rule on its orderliness. The sponsor will then be allowed one\nminute to speak to each amendment before I put the question to the House. ","index":"01408","speaker":""},{"html":"����� For\nconcurrence and third reading, the minister will move the motion, and I will\nthen immediately put the question without debate. ","index":"01409","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> The honourable member for St.&nbsp;Boniface, to move his first\namendment. ","index":"01410","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDougald </b><b><a name=\"_Toc21700464\">Lamont</a></b><b>�(St. Boniface):</b> I move, second